SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates May 11, 2026, as Artists at the Capitol Day
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Monday, May 11, 2026, as Artists at the Capitol Day.
3 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Art Education Association (LAEA) inspires and
4 empowers art educators by fostering creativity, advancing professional growth, championing
5 leadership, and advocating for the transformative power of the arts in every community; and
6 WHEREAS, LAEA annually presents eight awards to art educators who demonstrate
7 exceptional dedication to fostering creativity, community, advocacy, and dynamic learning
8 for Louisiana scholars; and
9 WHEREAS, award candidates are nominated by their colleagues and supervisors,
10 and nominations are reviewed by the LAEA Board of Directors; the board consists of fifteen
11 members who represent a diverse range of art education experience, from pre-K through the
12 university level, across the state; and
13 WHEREAS, LAEA honorees are recognized at the State Fall Conference, the
14 National Art Education Convention, and the state capitol; and
15 WHEREAS, the 2025 LAEA award recipients are Kelly Adkinson of East Baton
16 Rouge Parish, Southeastern Region Elementary Art Educator of the Year; Ange Riehl of
17 Lafayette Parish, LAEA Art Educator of the Year; Ashley Comeaux-Foret of St. Charles
18 Parish, LAEA Elementary Art Educator of the Year; Savannah Dominique of St. Tammany
19 Parish, LAEA New to the Profession Educator of the Year; Alix Rogers of Lafayette Parish,
20 LAEA Preservice Art Educator of the Year; Aubrey Garcia of Caddo Parish, LAEA
21 Secondary Art Educator of the Year; Shelly Breaux of Lafayette Parish, LAEA Southeastern
